Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:51.20,ED01 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Hatasenakatta yakusoku wo idaite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.20,0:23:55.45,ED01 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}{\fad(0,480)}Futari arukidasu
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.23,0:00:06.40,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is a science where one understands the structure of matter, breaks it down, then rebuilds it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.40,0:00:12.03,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is not an all-powerful technique,\Nas one cannot create something out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:17.83,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.83,0:00:22.54,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,This is the concept of equivalent exchange, the fundamental basis of alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.16,0:00:27.17,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a taboo in alchemy. Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.17,0:00:29.50,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,One must not commit this act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.55,0:02:08.77,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,In the city of Lior, a High Priest of Leto deceived people through the use of the Philosopher's Stone and alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:13.57,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al, who ventured into the church, stopped the High Priest's plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:17.61,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,However, the Philosopher's Stone was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.32,0:02:20.74,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,"Get up and take a step. Walk forward."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.24,0:02:24.87,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed's words pierced Rose's chest, who had lost all hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.74,0:02:29.75,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But, those words were also meant for themselves, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:45.76,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You're Basque Gran, the "Iron Blood Alchemist", aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:47.22,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.68,0:02:51.56,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists who go against God's path...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.27,0:02:53.56,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,...shall perish!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.77,0:02:59.78,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}you're{\i0} the killer who only goes after State Alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:00.53,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:04.58,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,You picked... the wrong opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:18.34,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,You're fast! But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:22.89,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.10,0:03:29.68,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,How foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:40.82,Default,Basque,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:42.70,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:57.04,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Another State Alchemist?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.59,0:04:00.01,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like quite a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:02.30,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,You have to be careful, too, Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.01,0:04:05.80,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,You may be his next target.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.01,0:04:06.89,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:15.06,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Führer President!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.06,0:04:16.27,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.11,0:04:20.11,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:24.57,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes, are you in charge of dealing with this matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.57,0:04:25.24,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.74,0:04:28.62,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,If there are people whom you require assistance from, request them immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:32.62,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,We must bring the iron hammer down on the traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:34.83,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.17,0:04:39.63,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Breda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:40.63,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:45.01,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... The Colonel must have been procrastinating again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:48.47,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Havoc, do half of these for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:50.64,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,I've got my hands full over here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.14,0:04:53.31,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, who is this again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:54.64,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's Lieutenant Yoki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.27,0:04:59.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He's a little rascal who was lining his pockets with the authority he was given at the coal mines of Youswell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:04.07,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He's currently on the run after having\Nhis actions exposed by the Elric Brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:06.95,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Sergeant Fuery, how is the radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:09.87,Default,Fuery,0000,0000,0000,,The receiver is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.87,0:05:11.45,Default,Fuery,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to replace some parts...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:17.33,Default,Fuery,0000,0000,0000,,Edward-kun! Alphonse-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:19.38,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:21.09,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The Colonel has been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.01,0:05:26.22,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The matter in Lior is settled all thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:27.68,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to express my gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.68,0:05:30.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't for you or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.80,0:05:33.93,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,And, was the search for\Nthe Philosopher's Stone a failure again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:39.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The stone was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:43.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But the power was unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.65,0:05:46.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He transmuted a huge chimera, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:49.49,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how you could use the stone to make something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.49,0:05:53.58,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really familiar with the field of\NBiological Alchemy, so I wouldn't know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:55.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm a little curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.12,0:06:00.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If we put our effort into researching it,\Nwe may find something useful in getting our bodies back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:01.08,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:04.05,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Then, how about seeking help from a specialist?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.05,0:06:04.92,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.59,0:06:08.88,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The Sewing-Life Alchemist, Shou Tucker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:11.09,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He is a scholar in chimera Transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.09,0:06:12.18,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll introduce you to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.43,0:06:14.22,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} going to go out of your way to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:17.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a trap! There's definitely more than meets the eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:18.98,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me with those suspicious eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:21.36,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,We're even after that case in Lior!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:24.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It just feels disgusting to know that I owe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.73,0:06:32.87,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Tucker became a State Alchemist two years ago after transmuting a chimera that understood human language.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:35.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Understood human language"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It could speak?! The chimera?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.16,0:06:40.62,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Apparently, it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:42.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Just one sentence...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.54,0:06:44.88,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to die."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:49.67,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It never ate afterwards and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.47,0:06:56.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What a huge house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.94,0:07:02.85,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,B-Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.85,0:07:06.94,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, we've got a lot of visitors!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:10.61,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Nina, we have to keep the dog tied down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:15.58,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.58,0:07:19.20,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,This house has been in a mess ever since my wife left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.09,0:07:29.63,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Well, pleasure to meet you, Edward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:32.76,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Shou Tucker, the Sewing-Life Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:36.43,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He is interested in the transmutation of living organisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.43,0:07:38.81,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He said he would love to have\Nthe honor of seeing your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.81,0:07:40.93,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, that's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:43.19,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,One thing, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.94,0:07:47.23,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd like for me to show you my hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:50.11,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to need to see yours, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.86,0:07:53.11,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what being an alchemist is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.74,0:07:56.49,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you interested in the transmutation of the living organisms, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.53,0:07:59.37,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well... he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:00.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:05.33,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Transmutation of your mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.08,0:08:07.84,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,As an eleven year old child?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:13.38,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see. So that's why you're called "The Fullmetal Alchemist"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:16.85,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,You've experienced a tough past, haven't you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.39,0:08:24.85,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure whether I could be of any help at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:28.19,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,but please take a look at my laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.78,0:08:34.03,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.03,0:08:36.16,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, this is a little embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:43.79,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,People call me the "authority" on chimeras, but in reality, it's not really going very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.50,0:08:48.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:51.34,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,That's the reference room. Feel free to take a look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.59,0:08:54.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Then I'll start with this shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:56.38,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll start with that one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.93,0:08:59.76,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be returning to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.76,0:09:02.10,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send someone to pick them up in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:07.69,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, he's really into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.69,0:09:10.11,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,He can't even hear what's going on around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.11,0:09:15.03,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I guess geniuses really do exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:42.81,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Up high! Up high!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al, what the heck are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.73,0:09:49.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Nina seemed like she wanted someone to play with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:53.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what the heck do you think we're here for-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:10:01.12,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Alexander wants someone to play with, too, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:04.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've got some guts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.95,0:10:08.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that even when hunting rabbits, lions put forth their fullest effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:14.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I, Edward Elric, shall deal with you with all of my physical and spiritual might!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:16.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You damn dog!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.72,0:10:22.22,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Yo Boss, I've come to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.14,0:10:26.68,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:30.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Eh, just taking a break from research...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:33.61,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Did you manage to get good data?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.28,0:10:37.53,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome to visit tomorrow, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.15,0:10:39.74,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,You'll come visit again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.66,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play tomorrow, all right, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.66,0:10:42.32,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:47.58,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right, Mr. Tucker, I've got a message for you from the Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.58,0:10:51.58,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,He told me to tell you, "It's almost the day of the assessment. Don't forget."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.50,0:10:54.84,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:10:56.25,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.05,0:11:03.30,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.85,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,What's an "assessment"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.93,0:11:09.06,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:15.27,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,A State Alchemist has to report the results of his experiments once a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:20.86,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy couldn't get a good evaluation last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.86,0:11:25.41,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,If Daddy messes up this year,\NDaddy won't be a State Alchemist anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:26.79,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:29.00,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.00,0:11:31.33,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,You're always studying so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.42,0:11:35.75,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I've got to do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.67,0:11:40.38,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,This... is my last chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:52.10,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, your mother left home two years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.94,0:11:55.77,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy told me that she went back to her parents' home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:12:01.11,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... it must be kind of lonely for you,\Nbeing alone with your daddy in a big house like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:03.11,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:07.03,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy's really nice, and I've got Alexander with me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.83,0:12:13.04,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,But... Daddy's always at his lab these days, so..
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.42,0:12:15.13,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'm kind of lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:25.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, my shoulders have gotten a little stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.34,0:12:27.68,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you exercise a bit, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.01,0:12:29.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds kind of nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.64,0:12:31.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:34.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Accompany me on my exercises!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:36.40,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:44.15,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:46.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Watch this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:48.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:50.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:01.92,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.30,0:13:06.22,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, Alexander!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:09.47,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,"It's almost the day of the assessment. Don't forget."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.52,0:13:21.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,But... why does he only target State Alchemists?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:25.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,If the army is his target, he can just attack soldiers indiscriminately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:30.37,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Since Alchemists possess special abilities, they're not easy to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:33.62,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,And one with a state qualification should be much tougher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.16,0:13:36.58,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's the qualification that's the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:37.25,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:40.46,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,An immense reward and various privileges.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:43.13,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Many are envious of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:44.88,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:48.64,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,"Alchemists, work for the good of the public."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:51.93,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists, who are supposed to be searching for the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.93,0:13:56.06,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,turn into the army's human weapons\Nas soon as they earn their state qualifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.02,0:13:59.52,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,And also, after that civil war in Ishbal,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.52,0:14:02.61,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,there are many who hold a grudge against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:07.07,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,Reporting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.61,0:14:16.79,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}Yesterday, around 9:30{\fscx75\fscy75}PM{\r}, many station employees witnessed a man with a large scar on his face at Central City Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.83,0:14:18.41,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Station?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.41,0:14:20.12,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Did he run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.00,0:14:27.13,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Our lives before I got my state qualification were terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.92,0:14:29.38,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,We were so poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:34.43,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,My wife couldn't stand living in conditions like that, and she left our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:39.10,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I need to pass the assessment, no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.85,0:14:44.27,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I don't ever want to return to those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.27,0:14:46.23,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.23,0:14:51.07,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,If they tell you "No", Alexander and I will go and scold the higher-ups!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.53,0:14:54.33,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Nina sure is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:58.41,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Nina... what do you say we play together tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.87,0:15:00.00,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:01.17,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:02.58,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.67,0:15:07.30,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Alexander, Daddy said he'd play with us tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:20.06,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Mr. Tucker!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:21.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be using your place again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:23.65,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.65,0:15:27.03,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tucker?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.03,0:15:29.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.65,0:15:32.95,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tucker?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:34.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you {\i1}are{\i0} here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.87,0:15:36.70,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:40.91,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,It's complete. The finished product.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:44.54,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,A chimera that understands human language.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.30,0:15:48.25,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:52.30,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,This person is Edward. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:55.30,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Ed...ward...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.47,0:15:57.93,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I'm so proud of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.93,0:16:00.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing... it really did talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.23,0:16:04.56,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Now I won't have to lose my state qualification.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:08.48,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Ed...ward...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:13.74,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Ed...ward...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:16.32,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Ed...ward...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.24,0:16:18.91,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,O...nii...chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:29.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tucker...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:32.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get your state qualification again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:36.14,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,It was two years ago, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:39.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And when did your wife leave you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:42.89,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:45.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask you another question?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:48.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nina and Alexander...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.40,0:16:49.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.74,0:16:56.11,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like sharp brats like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:16:59.12,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.12,0:17:00.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's how it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.91,0:17:02.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've done it, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.83,0:17:04.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was your wife two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.83,0:17:09.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,and this time, you used your daughter and your dog to transmute a chimera!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.04,0:17:13.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Since there are limits to animal experimentation, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:16.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It must be a breeze if you use a human!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:19.80,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's there to get angry about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:24.60,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,The mankind's advances are the product of many experiments on humans, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:26.27,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a scientist, too, then you should-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:27.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't screw around with me!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.69,0:17:30.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think something like this will be forgiven?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:34.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Something like this... toying with human life?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.03,0:17:36.70,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Human life?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:39.62,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, human life, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:41.78,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Fullmetal Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.78,0:17:45.16,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Your limbs and your younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:49.88,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't those the results of what you're saying right now? Toying with human life?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.88,0:17:50.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,NO!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.63,0:17:56.01,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,We're the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.01,0:17:57.88,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,You and I!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:17:58.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're not!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:00.51,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.51,0:18:03.68,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,There was a possibility in front of us, so we tested it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:06.27,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we knew it was taboo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.27,0:18:07.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.52,0:18:09.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.44,0:18:12.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:14.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.82,0:18:17.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I... I!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:18.24,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:21.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,If you go any further, he'll die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.71,0:18:34.55,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Da...ddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:36.76,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.30,0:18:39.05,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Da...ddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.55,0:18:40.55,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.64,0:18:47.81,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:52.73,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We can't change you back to normal with our powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:57.07,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.24,0:18:59.36,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Let's... play.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:01.07,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:03.99,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I made it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.99,0:19:07.08,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,With this, I can continue being a State Alchemist...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:21.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,State Alchemist, my ass...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:22.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stop kidding yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:26.89,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Let's... play.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.48,0:19:31.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,DAMMIT!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:38.73,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,If something such as an act of the Devil exists in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.73,0:19:41.65,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,this case is just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:43.91,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The Devil, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.57,0:19:51.37,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But if it is an order, State Alchemists must make\Ntheir move, without hesitation, to take human lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:54.04,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If it's about handling human lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:57.75,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,there really isn't much difference between where we stand and what Mr. Tucker did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.42,0:20:02.93,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You were aware of that, and yet you chose this path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.76,0:20:08.68,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right, Fullmetal?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:17.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll run into incidents like this in the future again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:20.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,There may be times when you have to soil your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.44,0:20:24.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to come to a stop like that every time it happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.61,0:20:28.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Whether they call me a dog of the military, or curse me as a devil,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:32.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al and I will get back our bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:34.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.29,0:20:36.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're neither devils,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:39.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,nor gods at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.30,0:20:41.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.26,0:20:46.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're just humans!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.35,0:20:52.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Puny, powerless humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.10,0:20:56.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...who can't even save one little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:02.11,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why no one understands us...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.90,0:21:03.74,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,...Nina...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:12.91,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You're Shou Tucker, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:14.12,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.12,0:21:17.54,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like... you're not from the military!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.00,0:21:19.46,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,How did you get in?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.46,0:21:21.59,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,There should have been military policemen stationed out front!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.05,0:21:25.47,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists, who go against God's path...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.97,0:21:29.51,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,...shall perish!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.40,0:21:39.86,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Da...ddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.07,0:21:43.53,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Da...ddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.19,0:21:45.86,Default,chimera,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.11,0:21:48.41,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,How miserable...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:52.37,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,But now that you are in a state like that,\Nthere is no way to return you to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.49,0:21:56.87,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, leave this world in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.84,0:22:03.75,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,God,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.38,0:22:09.14,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,two souls have just returned to your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.97,0:22:17.27,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Please usher them into your broad bosom,\Nand grant rest and salvation to their miserable souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.23,0:24:01.47,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The rain pours down in East City.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.01,0:24:04.21,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Still grief-stricken over Nina's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.21,0:24:07.75,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al are attacked by the mysterious man, Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:12.26,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,In a life-or-death crisis, Ed makes a desperate decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.05,0:24:17.56,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.56,0:24:20.14,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 5, Rain of Sorrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.50,0:24:26.35,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Will he be ready to accept the decision brought on by desperation?
